==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spittle
<hw>Spit"tle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Spit</er> to
spade.]</ety> <def>To dig or stir with a small spade.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spittle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Spittle
<hw>Spit"tle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small sort of spade.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spittle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Spittle
<hw>Spit"tle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Spit</er> to eject from
the mouth: cf. <er>Spattle</er>, and AS. <ets>sp⟦amac⟧tl</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The thick, moist matter which is secreted by the salivary glands;
saliva; spit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spittle insect</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Cuckoo spit</cref> <sd>(b)</sd>, under
<er>Cuckoo</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spittly</ent>⟦br⟧
